    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm afraid that you're right, @spikecurtis .\r\n\r\n`cliui.Select` and `survey.AskOne` do not play well with our PTY test. `AskOne` should wait for hitting \"Enter\", but apparently it does not.\r\n\r\nThe outcome is similar to not checking for parameter names and values at all:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nmatches := []string{\r\n// stringParameterName, \"\",\r\n// \"> third_option\", \"second_option\",\r\n\"Planning workspace...\", \"\",\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n/Users/mtojek/code/coder/cli/update_test.go:617: 2023-09-18 16:06:11.451: cmd: matched \"Planning workspace...\" = \"string_parameter\\r\\n\\r\\n> first_option\\r\\nPlanning workspace...\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe may wait for `> first_option`, and then sneak `second_option`, but this is basically a race condition.\r\n\r\nSumming up, I will check if we can find a workaround for the survey library. If not, then I will adjust tests to always pick up the first option. It seems to be an already [adopted pattern](https://github.com/coder/coder/blob/main/cli/cliui/select.go#L106-L110).",
